  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Quality Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities</strong> include the following (other duties may be assigned):</p><ul><li>Lead investigations into root cause analysis and corrective action reports (8D) for customers. Collaborate with other departments and SPT sites to resolve issues.</li><li>Support continuous improvement initiatives to improve yield and reduce scrap cost.</li><li>Support 5S improvement through regular audits and Gemba walks.</li><li>Investigate and take corrective action in response to process excursions.</li><li>Prepare quality reports and hold regular quality communication sessions with manufacturing staff to promote quality education.</li><li>Train QA inspectors on good quality practices, data collection, reporting, and feedback.</li><li>Prepare documentation such as Standard Operating Procedures (SOPs), Work Instructions, and One Point Lessons (OPL) to support quality improvement activities.</li><li>Conduct Measurement Systems Analysis (MSA) on critical production measurement devices and ensure all devices are fit for purpose.</li><li>Support ISO 9001 and ISO 14001 audits.</li><li>Collaborate with colleagues from various departments in cross-functional team activities<br /></li></ul><p><strong>Education / Qualification</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in mechanical or Electronics/Electrical Engineering.</li><li>LSS Green Belt preferred.</li></ul><p></p><p><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 4 years of post-graduate experience in Semiconductor, Electronic Manufacturing, Medical Equipment, or related industries.</li><li>Systematic and analytical problem-solving skills; experienced in the 8D process.</li><li>Good working knowledge of Statistical Process Control (SPC), MSA, FMEA, and statistical techniques.</li><li>Excellent communication skills and a strong team player.</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office.</li><li>Knowledgeable in ISO 9001 and ISO 14001 standards.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Core Competencies</strong></p><ul><li>Strong team player.</li><li>Highly customer focused.</li><li>Practical, solution-oriented approach to problem-solving.</li><li>Ability to learn new concepts, methods, and techniques.</li><li>Self-motivated; proactively seeks opportunities for improvement and acts without waiting for instruction.</li><li>Highly responsive; understand the need for speed of action.</li><li>Follow through to ensure results are achieved.</li></ul>",
